What is this ‘disjunctive existence' of two contradictories, upon which the truth of the proposition depends?

Disiunctive existence is existence that is indifferent

to the subjects in which it occurs;

in saying ‘One of these must be true', we predicate existence unitedly, but indifferently of either.
